# clang-format configuration for asm-test — the project's intended C style.
#
# The existing tree is hand-formatted to this intent, but is deliberately NOT
# bulk-reformatted: a few function signatures, macros, and trailing comments run
# a hair past the column limit by hand for readability, and the asm-heavy headers
# (include/asm.h, the ASM_FUNC macros) read better untouched. So `make fmt-check`
# is INFORMATIONAL (like `make tidy`/clang-tidy) — it reports drift without
# gating. Run `make fmt` to normalize NEW code before sending a change; editors
# that auto-format on save will pick this up so new C converges on one style.
#
# Promote fmt-check to a gate only after a reviewed, one-shot `make fmt` pass.
---
Language: Cpp
BasedOnStyle: LLVM
IndentWidth: 4
ContinuationIndentWidth: 4
ColumnLimit: 80
PointerAlignment: Right
# The tree keeps comments at their hand-wrapped widths (some intentionally a few
# columns over 80); don't let the formatter re-flow prose.
ReflowComments: false
# Match the manual column-aligned macro tables (e.g. the EMU_* address map).
AlignConsecutiveMacros: Consecutive
